1948;;The Strawberry Roan;;American;;John English;;Gene Autry, Gloria Henry;;western;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Strawberry_Roan;;Joe is paralyzed by a wild horse, a strawberry roan. His father, Walt, tries to kill the horse in anger but is unsuccessful and the horse escapes. Autry, who stopped Walt from killing the animal, is asked to leave the ranch. He finds the horse and trains it in the hopes of returning it to Joe to give him the will to overcome his disability.